  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>basil</strong> leaves from the stalks, chop the stalks finely and set the leaves aside for later</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot of boiled water over a high heat with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, add the <strong>lasagne sheets </strong>one at a time with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> in between them<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(this prevents them sticking together)</p>\r\n<p>Cook them for 5-7 min or until they've softened but not fully cooked and once drained, lay the <strong>lasagne sheets</strong> out separately, so they don't overlap each other</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>kale</strong> leaves from&nbsp;their tough inner stalks and chop them finely, discarding the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Heat a pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 3 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>kale</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and cook for 5 min or until the kale has wilted</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir for 2-3 min until a sandy coloured paste is formed - this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>milk</strong> gradually into the roux</p>\r\n<p>Whisk&nbsp;constantly for 4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, then remove from the heat, add the&nbsp;<strong>basil</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stalks</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar&nbsp;</strong>and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Crumble the <strong>feta</strong> into the softened&nbsp;<strong>kale&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Lightly oil an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Divide the<strong> kale and feta mixture</strong>&nbsp;between the lasagne sheets, then roll the filled<strong> lasagne sheets</strong>&nbsp;up tightly like a cigar - this is your <strong>canelloni&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>canelloni</strong> to your <strong>oven-proof&nbsp;dish</strong> with the seams facing down, pour the <strong>sauce</strong> over and top with the<strong> grated cheddar&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/822.-step-6-x200.jpg",
